Ten thousand years of calc-sinter deposition have created Nuorilang Waterfall. It was hit by a magnitude-7.0 earthquake in 2017 and damaged. But, after well-schemed restoring efforts that followed, it has been reborn. Although parts of the waterfall have been repaired and restored, the true healing can only be accomplished by the nature. About 'Journeys in Nature': Western Sichuan series Jiuzhaigou in southwest China's Sichuan Province has been regarded by locals as a "sacred mountain and water." Enjoy the panoramic view of the magnificent fairyland in the five-episode Western Sichuan series. For more Western Sichuan Series | Episode 1: The Iridescent Lake (Cover image a screenshot from the video) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)